modules.description: Converts server identifiers to strings, establishes and terminates network connections, and checks server status with a defined delay. Operates on server, connection, and serverid types. Used to manage real-time server monitoring and communication tasks.

Manages reusable resources with validation, cleanup, and concurrency control. Works with arbitrary resource types and supports creating, validating, and disposing of elements. Used for efficiently handling database connections, where resources are reused, checked for validity, and cleaned up after use.

Converts server identifiers to strings, establishes and terminates connections, and checks server status with a defined delay. Operates on server identifiers, server objects, and connection handles. Used to manage active connections and monitor server availability in real-time networking scenarios.

Manages pools of reusable resources, offering functions to acquire, release, and track usage of connections or threads. Works with structured data representing pools, resources, and their states. Used to efficiently handle database connections or server clusters under high load.

manages reusable resources with validation, cleanup, and concurrency, supporting arbitrary types and operations like creation, checking, and disposal. It handles server identifiers, connection establishment, and status checks, enabling real-time monitoring and efficient connection management. Operations include converting identifiers to strings, maintaining active connections, and enforcing delays between status checks. Examples include reusing database connections, validating server availability, and managing network resources with controlled access.
